-- allium: 3
-- specs/cuda-native-dispatch/multi_device_graph_cache.allium
--
-- Status: PLACEHOLDER. Bound by PHASE_CUDA_NATIVE_DISPATCH.md
-- commit C5 (multi-device graph cache extension).
--
-- Scope: the multi-device cudaGraph_t cache. Key is
-- (topology_hash, device_layout, n_seq) — extending the existing
-- per-context cuda_graphs cache (ggml-cuda/common.cuh:858-969,
-- currently keyed on topology_hash alone). Cache hit must replay
-- bit-identically to the original capture. Eviction policy: FIFO
-- bounded by GGML_CUDA_GRAPH_MAX (existing constant).
--
-- Why this spec exists: PD2 confirmed multi-device single-graph
-- capture works. With cross-device deps embedded in one graph, the
-- per-token replay overhead drops from N kernel launches × 3
-- backends to ONE cudaGraphLaunch. The cache makes this amortize
-- across topology hits. The spec binds correctness of the cache
-- under repeated capture/replay cycles.
--
-- Existing graph cache pattern in tree:
--   ggml-cuda.cu:5176  ggml_cuda_get_graph() find/insert
--   ggml-cuda/common.cuh:888 std::unordered_map<uint64_t,...>
--   "too many updates → disable graph" guard at line ~5212 (4+
--    consecutive cudaGraphExecUpdate failures evicts and falls
--    back to capture-on-every-call for that key)
--
-- The C5 extension keeps the same map shape but extends the key
-- type to include device_layout (which devices are active in this
-- graph) and n_seq (the dispatched-stream-count axis). Same find/
-- insert/erase semantics, same eviction policy.
--
-- Includes:
--   - External entity for the cache (GraphCache, GraphKey,
--     GraphValue).
--   - Contract CacheKeyUniqueness — distinct logical graphs hash
--     to distinct keys; key collisions are impossible by
--     construction (topology + device_layout + n_seq forms a
--     total characterization).
--   - Contract ReplayBitIdentical — cudaGraphLaunch on a cached
--     graph produces byte-identical output to the original capture
--     given the same inputs.
--   - Contract EvictionPreservesCorrectness — FIFO eviction up
--     to GGML_CUDA_GRAPH_MAX, then re-capture on next miss.
--
-- CODE REFS:
--   ik_llama.cpp/ggml/src/ggml-cuda.cu:5150     graph_compute entry
--   ik_llama.cpp/ggml/src/ggml-cuda.cu:5176     ggml_cuda_get_graph
--   ik_llama.cpp/ggml/src/ggml-cuda/common.cuh:888  cuda_graphs map
--   ik_llama.cpp/ggml/src/ggml-cuda.cu:5212     "too many updates" guard
--
-- TBD: write the cache state machine + binding invariants when C5
-- lands.

allium 3

